name: Jackrabbit Content Repository
description:
Apache Jackrabbit is a fully conforming implementation of the Content Repository for Java Technology API (JCR). A content repository is a hierarchical content store with support for structured and unstructured content, full text search, versioning, transactions, observation, and more.

See also:

  • JCRSITE: Jackrabbit web site and other project-level resources
  • OCM: Jackrabbit Object Content Mapping
  • JCRRMI: Jackrabbit JCR-RMI
  • JCRCL: Jackrabbit JCR Classloader
  • JCRBENCH: Jackrabbit JCR Benchmark
  • JCRSERVLET: Jackrabbit JCR Servlets
  • JCRTCK: Jackrabbit JCR Tests
  • OAK: Jackrabbit Oak
  • JCRVLT: Jackrabbit FileVault
